        "text": "<@UCUSW7WVD> That's an important point that I'd expect to be raised by postmodern critics of architecture: the power relation between the architect-designer and the people who will later live or work in the building.\n\nAnother example is Le Corbusier's \"Villa Savoye\" that <@UDCLA1HU4> mentions. It was actually a pain to live in. The construction techniques of the time were not up to Le Corbusier's dreams, and as a result there were lots of problems, in particular leaks in various places that nobody managed to fix.",
