                                "text": "As software designers, we are often using abstractions to hide the internals of a system from its users (or other developers). But such abstractions often hide contradictions that the implementors had to resolve in some, often imperfect way. If the abstractions do not leave any hint of such complexities, it is easy to hit their limitations and use them in a way in which they break."
                            }
